tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild anemia (low hemoglobin) with otherwise normal red cell indices and counts. Leukocyte and platelet counts are within normal limits, but there is a markedly elevated platelet distribution width, which may indicate increased platelet size variability, possibly due to reactive or regenerative processes. No acute hematological abnormalities are evident; clinical correlation is recommended.
